  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "瑞士起司模型 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-swiss-cheese-model",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / safety / defense / incidents</p>\n    <h1>瑞士起司模型</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Swiss Cheese Model</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">事故往往不是單一道防線失效，而是多層防護各自的小漏洞剛好排成一條通道，讓風險一路穿透。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要幫你把『哪個人做錯』和『哪些防線一起漏了』拆開，讓事故分析從找單點改成看穿透路徑。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>安全模型 / 多層防線</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Accidents happen when holes in multiple defenses align</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>防線層數、漏洞型態、同時失效條件、隔離能力</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在 postmortem 與 safety review 裡用多層防線視角找真正的系統缺口</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>防線</span>\n      <span>漏洞</span>\n      <span>對齊</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>真正危險的不是一個洞，而是很多洞剛好排成一直線</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">瑞士起司模型之所以常被引用，是因為它用很直觀的方式描述多層保護如何一起失守。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>單層防線幾乎永遠不完美；真正的安全來自缺陷不會同時對齊，而不是幻想每層都零漏洞。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先列防線</strong>\n        <p>先問系統有哪些層次在擋風險，而不是只看最後失敗點。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再辨洞的性質</strong>\n        <p>有些漏洞是長期 latent condition，有些是當下 active failure。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後看穿透路徑</strong>\n        <p>事故不是洞存在就會發生，而是多個洞在同一時刻被串起來。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一場看似很多人都失手的事故開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這個模型最有用的地方，是把『連環失誤』翻成『多層保護沒有互相補位』。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>需求澄清沒做好、測試治具剛好漏一項、review 沒觸及邊界條件、發布門檻又放寬，結果問題一路通過每一道門。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>每一層單看都像偶發小缺口，但事故發生在這些缺口剛好排成可穿透的時候。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">多層防線各有漏洞</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">漏洞在特定時機對齊</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">風險一路穿透成事故</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>瑞士起司模型最有價值的提醒是：別問哪片起司最爛，先問為什麼洞能連成一線。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看防線失守的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">若想用這個模型分析事故，通常要同時看這四件事。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>潛在條件</strong>\n        <p>長期存在但不顯眼的制度、資源或設計缺口，平常就把洞挖好了。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>活躍失誤</strong>\n        <p>當下的操作失誤、誤判或違規，常是最後被看見的那一層。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>防線相依</strong>\n        <p>如果多層保護彼此過度依賴，同一種錯就可能一起穿透。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>恢復能力</strong>\n        <p>即使前面漏了，後面是否還有機會檢出、隔離、回滾或降級。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>防線層</th>\n            <th>看起來像</th>\n            <th>洞可能長在哪</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>需求與設計</td>\n            <td>規則寫得有</td>\n            <td>邊界條件沒被明講或被誤讀</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>測試與驗證</td>\n            <td>有 test 就安全</td>\n            <td>場景覆蓋不夠、治具模型太理想</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Review 與流程 gate</td>\n            <td>有人簽名就算過</td>\n            <td>注意力被瑣事帶走，關鍵假設沒被追問</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>發布與監控</td>\n            <td>可以上就先上</td>\n            <td>缺少及時偵測與回滾通道</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼事故後人總想只抓最後那個洞</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為最後一個可見錯誤最容易被指出來，但它通常不是整條穿透路徑的全部。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>最後觸發者最顯眼</strong>\n        <p>人會自然把注意力放在事故前最後一個動作或最後一個人身上。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>潛在條件較無戲劇性</strong>\n        <p>制度與資源缺口平常安靜存在，事後比較難被直覺當成主角。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>單點責任故事較簡單</strong>\n        <p>把事故濃縮成一個人的失誤，比承認防線群整體設計不足更省力。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">這個模型不否認個別失誤，而是要求你把個別失誤放回更完整的防線脈絡裡看。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把多層防線思維帶回 review 與發布</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對 firmware、infra 與安全關鍵流程來說，真正的防禦不是一關做滿，而是多關互補。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>發布流程</strong>\n        <p>requirements、unit test、integration test、staging 與 monitoring 都是不同層次的起司，不能假設其中一層萬能。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>硬體安全互鎖</strong>\n        <p>sensor、firmware、driver、UI 提示與人工檢查若有共同盲區，就可能在極端情境下一起漏。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>資安防禦</strong>\n        <p>ACL、驗證、監控與回應程序若共享同一錯誤假設，攻擊就能一次穿透多層。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>做事故檢討時，至少列出四層以上防線，逐層找出洞如何連線，而不是只找最後責任人。</li>\n      <li>最值得修的常不是『把最後一層再拉高』，而是讓不同防線不要共享同一盲點。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>別把模型縮成『每層都有洞所以算了』</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">瑞士起司模型不是宿命論，而是防線設計語言。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>既然每層都有洞，事故無可避免</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。真正目標是避免洞在同一時刻對齊，並提高穿透成本。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要多加幾層就安全</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>層數不是重點；若層與層共享同樣盲點，厚度再多也沒用。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這模型只適合飛安</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>任何多層防禦系統都可以借這種視角檢查自身。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>這場事故到底穿過了哪些起司</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放進每次 postmortem。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果最後那個人沒失手，前面哪一層其實仍然在漏</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你避免把責任全部壓在最後一個可見動作上。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>哪些防線的洞其實來自同一個根因</strong>\n        <p>若多層共享同樣的假設錯誤，補一層通常不夠。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可看 defense in depth、normal accident theory 與 postmortem analysis；也可以把這頁接到 safety review 模板。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 Swiss cheese model 的多層防線圖像為主，再補上 James Reason 與 defense in depth 的脈絡。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Swiss cheese model 條目整理了多層防線與漏洞對齊的經典圖像。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swiss_cheese_model\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Swiss Cheese Model</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>作者背景</strong>\n        <p>James Reason 條目可回看這個模型在人的錯誤與事故研究中的位置。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Reason\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">James Reason</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰做法</strong>\n        <p>Defense in depth 的概念能補上多層防線為何不能只靠單點完美。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defense_in_depth_(computing)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Defense in Depth</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後很適合把最近一次事故重畫成防線圖，看是哪些洞同時排直了，而不是只在最後一層做加厚。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
